Luis - There are several e-mail groups for the Vietnam vet, however, many are private in which you need to be invited in. Of the &quot;open to the public&quot;, there are two that comes to mind.<br><br>
The first is VWAR. You need to set up a blank e-mail page and in the address space, type this address:<br><br>
listserv@listserv.acsu.buffalo.edu<br><br>
In the Subject space, do not type anything!<br><br>
In the body, type the following:<br><br>
subscribe VWAR-L Luis Montanez<br><br>
You will get a confirmation e-mail back in which you send back with the word at the end: ok.<br><br>
Then you will be getting e-mail from this group. Folks on this list range from vets to protestors to civilians.<br><br>
There is also a Women's List by the name of Incountry-Women. They are composed of 'Nam nurses, donut dollies, Era vets, civilians and a few males. E-mail me if you wish to check out this list.
